`crates/ctx-scan/src` is the standalone CLI tool that maintains a `.context/` mirror of per-file/per-dir summaries for an arbitrary directory tree — not necessarily a git repo. Depending on this crate gets you four pipeline entry points (scan/check/update/prune) plus a `--stop-hook` mode for agent session integration; everything else is internal wiring the caller shouldn't need to know.

The pipeline is strictly staged and the stage order is load-bearing: `walker` produces the scope-filtered file list, `hash` diffs it against stored sidecars to produce `Staleness`, `reconcile` prunes orphaned mirror artifacts *before* any summarization (so rollups never absorb orphaned content), and only then does `runner::regenerate` call the model — in fixed order changed-leaves, then orphan-leaf removal, then stale dirs. `runner.rs` is where this sequencing lives and is the natural starting point for any pipeline change.

Two shared data contracts bind the children together: `Staleness` (staleness.rs) is produced by `hash`+`reconcile` and consumed by `render`, `cli`, and `runner` — its `needs_regeneration()` vs `is_fresh()` distinction is the single gate on whether the model gets called, and callers must use the former. `OrphanScan::artifacts_excluding` / `Staleness.orphan_artifacts` dedupe logic is duplicated across `runner::check_run`/`update_run` and must stay in sync with `reconcile`'s categorization. `render.rs`'s five staleness line-categories must match `Staleness`'s field names, and its cost-gate hint cross-references `ctx_summarize::runner::MAX_TARGETS` directly.

Cutting across everything: prompts load relative to process cwd, not the scanned tree (noted independently in `lib.rs`, `cli.rs`, `runner.rs` — easy to violate if refactored into one place). `.ctxignore` (seeded once from `.gitignore`) is the sole scope source, shared between `walker` and `ctx_summarize::fs::scope_matcher`. `cli.rs` and `main.rs` both encode mode-exclusivity/dispatch-order rules that must stay mirrored in `runner::*_run` naming. `contract.rs`'s `CONTRACT` string is asserted equal to actual CLI behavior by a test — edit CLI flags, edit that string too.